cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR 

The paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques to detect counterfeit identity documents. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with security and cryptography, which falls under the category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper proposes a mobile-server architecture, which involves machine learning algorithms, making it relevant to the category cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also proposes a crowdsourcing mode, which involves data collection and labeling, making it relevant to the category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves feature extraction techniques, which is relevant to the category cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
